'''Vomiting''' or '''nausea''' is a [[property|status affliction]] caused by eating 

*[[tripe]] as a non-orc non-caveman non-carnivore
*old [[egg]]s
*rotten [[tin]]s
*[[Clove of garlic|garlic]], while [[Polyself|polymorphed]] into an [[undead]] monster

After a while, it will cause you to become [[confused]], then [[stunned]], and finally vomit and lose 20 points of [[nutrition]].{{refsrc|src/timeout.c|211|nethack=3.6.2}} The final act of vomiting leaves you helpless for 2 turns, and actually cures [[food poisoning]], though you cannot count on vomiting before you die: vomiting takes 14 turns, while food poisoning will kill you in 10 + 1d9 turns.

If you are polymorphed into a [[rat]], you cannot vomit, but are still helpless for 2 turns. {{refsrc|src/mondata.c|439|nethack=3.6.2}}

You can cure the condition (and keep the nutrition) by:
* quaffing a blessed [[potion of healing]], a noncursed [[potion of extra healing]], or a noncursed [[potion of full healing]]{{refsrc|src/potion.c|1167|nethack=3.6.2}}
* applying a [[unicorn horn]]
* casting {{spell of|cure sickness}}{{refsrc|src/spell.c|1181|nethack=3.6.2}}{{refsrc|src/potion.c|1168|nethack=3.6.2}},
* eating a [[eucalyptus leaf]] 

When you are nauseated, you [[Exercise|abuse]] constitution once in every 5 turns (3 times in total).{{refsrc|src/attrib.c|506|nethack=3.6.2}}

{{upcoming|NetHack 3.7.0|Per {{commit|e9c813b6ba4a77727aa208191c17d6af039293c8}}, if you vomit while standing on an [[altar]] you will experience negative effects depending on the altar alignment and your [[alignment record]]. If the altar is co-aligned and your alignment record is greater than -[[rn2]](4), you lose one point of wisdom and one point of alignment record; otherwise, you lose 0-2 points of Luck, if your Luck is greater than -5.}}

==Messages==
You receive the following messages:{{refsrc|src/timeout.c|160|nethack=3.6.2}}

{{message|You are feeling mildly nauseated.|You are nauseated for 14 more turns.}}
{{message|You feel slightly confused.|You are nauseated for 11 more turns. You actually become confused for 2d4 (more) turns when the timeout reaches 8, then 6 turns.}}
{{message|You can't seem to think straight.|You are nauseated for 8 more turns. You actually become stunned for 2d4 (more) turns when the timeout reaches 6 turns.}}
{{message|You feel incredibly sick.|You are nauseated for 5 more turns.}}
{{message|You are about to vomit.|You are nauseated for 2 more turns.}}
{{message|You are about to hurl.|You are nauseated for 2 more turns while [[hallucinating]].}}
{{message|You vomit!|You vomit, leaving you helpless for 2 turns.}}
{{message|You hurl chunks!|You vomit while hallucinating.}}
{{message|Your [stomach] heaves convulsively!|You vomit while hungry to the point of fainting already. This still cures food poisoning.}}
{{message|Your jaw gapes convulsively.|You are polymorphed into a creature that cannot vomit.}}

==SporkHack==
In [[SporkHack]], drinking a glass of salt water can also make you vomit.

